@startuml

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
}

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
    DiamondBorderColor #856404
    StartColor #212529
    EndColor #212529
}
skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    TitleFontColor #212529
    TitleFontSize 13
}
skinparam ArrowColor #495057
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam NoteBorderColor #5BA4CF

title Agent Execution Loop

|Caller|
start
:Call **agent**(instructions, messages, tools, ?schema);

if (schema provided?) then (yes)
    :Instantiate **StructuredAnonymousAgent**\n(implements HasStructuredOutput);
else (no)
    :Instantiate **AnonymousAgent**\n(implements Agent, Conversational, HasTools\nuses Promptable trait);
endif

:Call **agent->prompt**(prompt, attachments,\n?provider, ?model, ?timeout);

|AnonymousAgent / Promptable|
:Promptable::prompt() invoked;
:Build **AgentPrompt**(agent, prompt,\nattachments, provider, model, timeout);
:Call **withModelFailover**(callback, provider, model);
:Resolve provider list via\n**getProvidersAndModels**() \n(checks method/attribute → falls back to config('ai.default'));

|Provider (GeneratesText)|
repeat
    :Resolve **Provider** instance\nvia Ai::textProviderFor();
    :Resolve model via **getDefaultModelFor**()\n(checks UseSmartestModel / UseCheapestModel / default);
    note right
        Failover loop iterates
        through provider/model pairs
    end note

    :Call **Provider->prompt**(AgentPrompt)\ninside try/catch(FailoverableException);

    :Generate **invocationId** (uuid7);
    :Build **middleware pipeline**\n(gatherMiddlewareFor: checks RemembersConversations,\nHasMiddleware, adds RememberConversation if applicable);
    :pipeline()->send(prompt)->through(middleware)->then(closure);

    fork
        :Dispatch **PromptingAgent** event;
    fork again
        :Collect messages\n(agent->messages() if Conversational)\nAppend new **UserMessage**(prompt, attachments);
    fork again
        :Register **onToolInvocation** callbacks\nvia listenForToolInvocations()\n(will dispatch InvokingTool / ToolInvoked events);
    end fork

    if (agent instanceof HasStructuredOutput?) then (yes)
        :Extract JSON schema\nvia agent->schema(JsonSchemaTypeFactory);
    else (no)
    endif

    |TextGateway|
    :Call **textGateway()->generateText**()\n(provider, model, instructions, messages,\ntools, schema, options, timeout);
    :Build HTTP request body via\n**buildTextRequestBody**();
    :HTTP POST → Provider API\n('responses' endpoint);
    :Validate response via\n**validateTextResponse**()\n(throw AiException on error);
    :Delegate to **parseTextResponse**() →\nenter **processResponse**();

    repeat
        :Extract: text, toolCalls, reasonings,\ncitations, usage, finishReason\nfrom response output;
        :Map tool calls via\n**mapToolCallsWithReasoning**()\n→ array<ToolCall(id, name, arguments,\nresultId, reasoningId, reasoningSummary)>;
        :Create **Step**(text, toolCalls, [],\nfinishReason, usage, meta)\nPush to $steps collection;
        :Append **AssistantMessage** to $messages;

        if (finishReason == ToolCalls\nAND toolCalls not empty\nAND steps.count < maxSteps?) then (yes — continue tool loop)
            note right
                maxSteps defaults to
                round(toolCount × 1.5)
            end note

            |Tool Execution|
            :executeToolCalls()\nforeach ToolCall in toolCalls;
            :findTool(name, tools);
            :Dispatch **InvokingTool** event\n(via invokingToolCallback);
            :Call **tool->handle**(new Request(arguments));
            :Dispatch **ToolInvoked** event\n(via toolInvokedCallback);
            :Collect result as string\n→ build **ToolResult**(id, name, arguments,\nresult, resultId);

            |TextGateway|
            :Update **Step** in $steps\nwith toolResults array;
            :Append **ToolResultMessage**\nto $messages;
            :Call **continueWithToolResults**()\nHTTP POST follow-up with\nprevious_response_id + tool results input;
            :Validate follow-up response via\n**validateTextResponse**();
            note right
                Recurse into processResponse()
                with new data and depth+1
            end note
        else (no — stop condition)
        endif
    repeat while (tool loop continues?) is (recurse)
    ->stop condition reached\n(FinishReason: Stop / Length / Error\nor maxSteps exceeded);

    :Aggregate allToolCalls + allToolResults\nfrom all steps;

    if (structured output?) then (yes)
        :Return **StructuredTextResponse**\n(structuredData, text, combinedUsage, meta);
    else (no)
        :Return **TextResponse**\n(text, usage, meta);
    endif

    :Attach .withMessages(messages)\n.withSteps(steps)\n.withToolCallsAndResults();

    |Provider (GeneratesText)|
    :Dispatch **AgentPrompted** event;

    if (FailoverableException thrown?) then (yes)
        :Dispatch **AgentFailedOver** event;
        note right
            Continue loop to
            next provider/model pair
        end note
    else (no)
        :Return **AgentResponse**\n(or StructuredAgentResponse)\nwith invocationId, text, usage, meta,\ntoolCalls, toolResults, steps, messages;
    endif
repeat while (try next provider?) is (failover)
->success;

|Caller|
:Receive **AgentResponse**\n(or StructuredAgentResponse);
stop

@enduml
